<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17680706-2">
               <interp inst="t17680706-2" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680706-2" type="year" value="1768"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680706-2" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17680706"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680706-2" type="date" value="17680706"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17680706-2-off7-c36" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-defend40 t17680706-2-off7 t17680706-2-verdict12"></join>
         
               <p>408. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17680706-2-defend40" type="defendantName">
                     Dorothy 
                     Allen 
                  <interp inst="t17680706-2-defend40" type="surname" value="Allen"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-defend40" type="given" value="Dorothy"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-defend40" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , <rs id="t17680706-2-deflabel6" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-defend40 t17680706-2-deflabel6"></join>, was indicted for <rs id="t17680706-2-off7" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-off7" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-off7" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a linen gown, value 9 s. a cotton gown, value 3 s. a silk cardinal, value 12 s. a duffel cardinal trimmed with furr, a linen apron, a cheque apron, a linen shirt, a pair of stockings, a black silk hat, and a pair of woman's silk shoes
            </rs>, the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17680706-2-victim42" type="victimName">
                     Peter 
                     Scott 
                  <interp inst="t17680706-2-victim42" type="surname" value="Scott"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-victim42" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-victim42" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-off7 t17680706-2-victim42"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17680706-2-cd8" type="crimeDate">May 24</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-off7 t17680706-2-cd8"></join>. ||</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680706-2-person43">
                  Esther 
                  Scott 
               <interp inst="t17680706-2-person43" type="surname" value="Scott"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person43" type="given" value="Esther"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person43" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am wife to 
               <persName id="t17680706-2-person44">
                  Peter 
                  Scott 
               <interp inst="t17680706-2-person44" type="surname" value="Scott"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person44" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person44" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , we live in <placeName id="t17680706-2-crimeloc9">Leather-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17680706-2-crimeloc9" type="placeName" value="Leather-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17680706-2-crimeloc9" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-off7 t17680706-2-crimeloc9"></join>, he is <rs id="t17680706-2-viclabel10" type="occupation">journeyman to Stoughton's warehouse</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-victim42 t17680706-2-viclabel10"></join>; on the 23d of May the prisoner came<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176807060003"></xptr> to breakfast with me, while I went out of an errand she took a pair of shoes; I missed them about an hour after she was gone; I went to see for her on the 24th in the morning about Sadler's Wells, <rs id="t17680706-2-deflabel11" type="occupation">she cries crabs and shrimps about</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-defend40 t17680706-2-deflabel11"></join>; I did not find her; I returned home about six, and found my room-door open, two drawers open, and a gown, cardinal, and hat missing from one, out of the other a purple and white gown, a coloured apron from the bed-post; I missed also a pair of worsted stockings of my husband's, and a lawn apron out of a clothes-basket, and a shirt and silk handkerchief; I lost other things, I thought she had taken them; I met a young woman, who told me such a woman as I described had been with her; I was directed to her house in Vine-street, Mutton-hill, Clerkenwell; she was upon her bed with my duffel cloak and coloured apron, that I lost from hanging behind my room door; she said she would down upon her knees if I would forgive her, and said she would tell me of the other things; I took her to a public-house, she confessed where she had carried them before Sarah Lake and 
               <persName id="t17680706-2-person45">
                  John 
                  Gibbons 
               <interp inst="t17680706-2-person45" type="surname" value="Gibbons"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person45" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person45" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (the cloak and apron produced and deposed to;) a shift, handkerchief, and apron I found in her lodgings; she went with me to Mr. Keden and Mr. Needham's, two pawnbrokers, where several things were pawned (produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680706-2-person46">
                  Sarah 
                  Lake 
               <interp inst="t17680706-2-person46" type="surname" value="Lake"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person46" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-person46" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the prisoner confess to the taking the things, and that some were pawned, and some at her lodgings, where they were found, by her directions.</p>
               <p>The two pawnbrokers deposed to the taking in the goods of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said she had nothing to say in her defence.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17680706-2-verdict12" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-verdict12" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17680706-2-punish13" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680706-2-punish13" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-2-defend40 t17680706-2-punish13"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
